<h1>Problem 1560 - 2023 ELMOSL, G7, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(\mathcal E\) be an ellipse with foci \(F_1\) and \(F_2\), and let \(P\) be a point on \(\mathcal E\). Suppose lines \(PF_1\) and \(PF_2\) intersect \(\mathcal E\) again at distinct points \(A\) and \(B\), and the tangents to \(\mathcal E\) at \(A\) and \(B\) intersect at point \(Q\). Show that the midpoint of \(\overline{PQ}\) lies on the circumcircle of \(\triangle PF_1F_2\).</p>
